    public class DiscreteDistPoisson
extends DiscreteDist<java.lang.Long>
    Poisson distributed stream of pseudo random integer numbers. The distribution specified by one parameter describing the mean value.

    • Constructor Detail

      • DiscreteDistPoisson

        public DiscreteDistPoisson(Model owner,
                           java.lang.String name,
                           double meanValue,
                           boolean showInReport,
                           boolean showInTrace)
        Creates a poisson distributed stream of pseudo random integer numbers. The parameter describes the mean value. Giving zero or negative values for the mean value will result in zero being returned by the sample() method.
        Parameters:
        owner - Model : The distribution's owner
        name - java.lang.String : The distribution's name
        meanValue - double : The mean double value for this distribution
        showInReport - boolean : Flag for producing reports
        showInTrace - boolean : Flag for producing trace output
